{"id":5959,"date":"2012-09-07T00:13:32","date_gmt":"2012-09-07T04:13:32","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=5959"},"modified":"2025-03-08T16:27:49","modified_gmt":"2025-03-08T12:27:49","slug":"hikmah-sulayman-ibn-dawud","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/07\/hikmah-sulayman-ibn-dawud\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Sulayman: Wisdom of Solomon, son of David"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u00a0\u201c<strong>There were two women each of whom had a child. A wolf came and took one of their children, so one woman said, &#8216;It has taken your child!&#8217; The other woman said, &#8216;No, rather it has taken your child!&#8217; They took their case to David who judged in favor of the older woman. Then, both of them went to Solomon, son of David, and told him about the matter. Solomon said, &#8216;Bring me a knife. I will cut him into two pieces.&#8217; The younger woman, &#8216;Do not do it, may Allah have mercy on you! It is her child!&#8217; Thus, Solomon judged in favor of the younger woman.&#8221;<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3426, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1720<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/strong><\/em> (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u00a0\u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0627\u0645\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u